issue.title: High number of installation warnings - vite
issue.body:
- This follows on from issue #1329 for the previous configuration using CRA, which has been replaced by vite.

## Description

Running `yarn install` produces a large number of warnings.

- [ ] [@material-ui/core](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@material-ui/core) - deprecated
- [ ] [@material-ui/icons@4.11.3](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@material-ui/icons)
- [ ] [@material-ui/lab](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@material-ui/lab) - deprecated
- [x] [@xstate/react@2.0.1](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@xstate/react)
- [ ] [aws-amplify](https://www.npmjs.com/package/aws-amplify)
- [x] [react-google-login@](https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-google-login) - deprecated
- [ ] [react-infinite-calendar@2.3.1](https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-infinite-calendar)
- [x] [@babel/plugin-proposal-private-property-in-object](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@babel/plugin-proposal-private-property-in-object) - deprecated
- [ ] [@cypress/code-coverage](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@cypress/code-coverage)
- [x] [@cypress/webpack-dev-server@1.8.4](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@cypress/webpack-dev-server) - should not need to be installed separately
- [x] [@percy/cypress@2.3.4](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@percy/cypress)
- [x] [eslint-config-react-app](https://www.npmjs.com/package/eslint-config-react-app)
- [ ] [express-graphql](https://www.npmjs.com/package/express-graphql) - deprecated

## Steps to reproduce

Clone repo and execute the following under Node.js `18.16.1`:

```bash
git clean -x -d -f
yarn install
```

## Expectation

There should be no installation warnings produced by `yarn install`.

pull_request.title: chore: fix some peer dependency warnings
pull_request.body:
Partially resolves https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress-realworld-app/issues/1403

- adds peer deps `@babel/core`, `@babel/plugin-syntax-flow`, `@babel/plugin-transform-react-jsx`, `webpack`
- replaces `react-google-login` with `@matheusluizn/react-google-login` to meet React 18 peer dependencies
- upgrades `@xstate/react` to `3.0.0`
- upgrades `@percy/cypress` to `3.2.1`
    -  removes `percyHealthCheck` usage. [Percy says that this isn't available or necessary past v2](https://www.browserstack.com/docs/percy/migration/steps)
- removes `@cypress/webpack-dev-server`

issue.title: chore: add light logo for Github README view
issue.body: Closes #1402 We're using `rwa-logo.svg` for our logo in the readme, which uses the [currentColor attribute](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/color_value#currentcolor_keyword) for its fill color, which should allow the fill to change with the context of where it is placed. It appears that this isn't working correctly in Github when it displays the README. To fix this, I created `rwa-logo-light.svg` which explicitly sets the fill colors to `white`, and added the suffixes that [Github will use to display each SVG depending on whether the user is in light mode or dark mode](https://github.blog/changelog/2021-11-24-specify-theme-context-for-images-in-markdown/). The downside to this approach is that some previewers (like the VSCode preview) do handle this correctly, so now they'll show two images side-by-side. I think it's worth the tradeoff to look better on Github though. **Github light mode** **Github dark mode**
